# TypeScript Patterns for Dashboard System

## Required Type Imports

Always import types from the dashboard types file:

```tsx
import {
  type BreadcrumbItem,
  type SidebarNavGroup,
  type SidebarNavItem,
} from '@/components/dashboard';
```

## Interface Definitions

### Navigation Types

From [types.ts](mdc:src/components/dashboard/types.ts):

```tsx
interface SidebarNavItem {
  title: string; // Display name & tooltip text
  href: string; // Navigation URL
  icon: LucideIcon; // Icon component (required for collapsed mode)
  badge?: string | number; // Optional badge (hidden when collapsed)
  disabled?: boolean; // Disable navigation
}

interface SidebarNavGroup {
  title: string; // Group heading (hidden when collapsed)
  items: SidebarNavItem[]; // Navigation items
}

interface BreadcrumbItem {
  title: string; // Display text
  href?: string; // Optional link (last item usually non-clickable)
}
```

### Component Props

```tsx
interface DashboardLayoutProps {
  children: React.ReactNode;
  sidebarNavigation: SidebarNavGroup[];
  breadcrumbItems?: BreadcrumbItem[];
}

interface DashboardSidebarProps {
  navigation: SidebarNavGroup[];
}

interface DashboardHeaderProps {
  breadcrumbItems?: BreadcrumbItem[];
}
```

## Icon Requirements

### LucideIcon Usage

All navigation items MUST include a LucideIcon:

```tsx
import { Home, Settings, Users } from 'lucide-react';

const navigation: SidebarNavGroup[] = [
  {
    title: 'Main',
    items: [
      {
        title: 'Dashboard',
        href: '/dashboard',
        icon: Home, // Required for tooltips in collapsed mode
      },
    ],
  },
];
```

## Type Safety Rules

1. **Always use the provided interfaces** - Don't create ad-hoc object types
2. **Icon prop is required** - Navigation items without icons will break in collapsed mode
3. **Optional href for last breadcrumb** - Current page breadcrumb typically has no href
4. **Badge can be string or number** - Handles both text badges and count badges
5. **Use type imports** - Import types with `type` keyword for better tree-shaking
